<br>
We have many buffs that we first gain as single target buffs and then get a group version of.  Having PoTG single target added to the game is very much in line with how our spells have advanced for a long time.<br>
<br>
They are in the process of working on casters, every change that they bring forward people are complaining about and not even seeing the advantages that it may offer.  Some are upset that spells are added to lower levels.<br>
<br>
I don't believe that these are the only changes we will see to caster balance in the druid line.  It will take time to work in all of the changes.  But is it necessary to throw every positive change back in their face?  <br>
<br>
I personally am happy for any mana reduction in our spell line.  There are times when you will only want the single target PoTG, even grouped, even in a raid one caster can die and need a rebuff at a time you don't want to spend the 1200 mana.  And there are times when you need to do something that only really requires one person and the buff will be great for those times.  Remember that level 59 druids are trying to heal and buff groups too and having to do it with many less options than level 60 druids.  Other classes have self only mana regen buffs, this is a plus to our class not a negative.<br>
<br>
I don't believe the way to achieve positive change to our class is to be negative and unpleasant about every thing that they add to or change, especially when some of the changes were specifically asked for by druids. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usanterre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Santerre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(3/13/02 11:25:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26729.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Single PotG on test spdat</span><hr size=1> Sobe, your premise assumes there is a fixed number of changes that can be made, and this "wastes" one.  Obviously if you gave me a choice of "would I rather have a cold-based RFS spell or single-target PoTG", I would choice a new ability over this.  But assuming this is not the case, and there are potential an unlimited number of changes that can be made, are you still opposed to it?  <br>
